article.headline: American 86, Army 58
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Andre Ingram scored 23 points Friday night, and Jason Thomas had 18 to lead American to an 86-58 victory over Army. The Eagles (13-7, 6-2 Patriot League) opened with a 12-4 run, led 47-31 at halftime and shot 52 percent for the game to win their third straight and seventh in eight games. American outrebounded Army 44-21. Colin Harris scored 16 points to lead the Black Knights (3-17, 1-7), whose seven conference losses have been by an average of 21 points. Army lost at home to American 72-37 on Jan. 21. The victory was the 72nd for coach Jeff Jones at American, tying him with current Maryland coach Gary Williams for fifth place on the school's all-time list. <
